instead of the one in the subplot title.

00:15:01.280 --> 00:15:03.059
Our team lead, or our team R lead

00:15:03.059 --> 00:15:05.479
was also not responsible for those ideas.

00:15:05.479 --> 00:15:07.099
We maybe would have come up with them.

00:15:07.099 --> 00:15:07.940
Who knows?

00:15:10.440 --> 00:15:11.280
So that's it.

00:15:11.280 --> 00:15:12.559
Here's my contact information.

00:15:12.559 --> 00:15:14.619
We have our blog post, our public repo

00:15:14.619 --> 00:15:16.080
of all of the data and the code

00:15:16.080 --> 00:15:18.140
if you want to recreate it for yourself.

00:15:18.419 --> 00:15:21.739
And happy to talk about other ways we could have done this.

00:15:21.739 --> 00:15:22.580
Thanks.

00:15:22.580 --> 00:15:27.580
All right, thank you so much, Olivia.

00:15:30.059 --> 00:15:30.900
Sure.

00:15:32.020 --> 00:15:34.780
Let's take a few questions from Slido.

00:15:34.780 --> 00:15:35.619
Okay.

00:15:35.619 --> 00:15:37.219
It'll appear on my phone.

00:15:37.219 --> 00:15:38.340
Go easy on me.

00:15:41.840 --> 00:15:44.419
Okay, this is from anonymous, and I get why.

00:15:44.419 --> 00:15:45.260
Oh, good.

00:15:46.260 --> 00:15:49.059
Weird flex preferring matplotlib to ggplot2,

00:15:49.059 --> 00:15:53.340
but why matplotlib and not seaborn or seaborn.object?

00:15:53.340 --> 00:15:56.059
I don't really have a reason for that.

00:15:56.059 --> 00:15:57.580
It was, you know, we gave ourselves a week

00:15:57.580 --> 00:16:01.320
to do this challenge, and we did what was familiar to us.

00:16:01.320 --> 00:16:04.039
I'm sure it's possible in seaborn.

00:16:05.260 --> 00:16:07.179
And, you know, again, I'm not here to say

00:16:07.179 --> 00:16:09.500
one package is better or one tool is better than the other.

00:16:09.500 --> 00:16:11.900
If you love ggplot, that makes you just as great

00:16:11.900 --> 00:16:13.500
of a data scientist as if you're one

00:16:13.500 --> 00:16:15.179
using matplotlib or seaborn.

00:16:16.900 --> 00:16:18.900
All right, Olivia, thank you so much.

00:16:18.900 --> 00:16:21.739
Let's give a round of applause for all the speakers again.

